Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 1/15/99

Spent time with Wayne to come up with a common plan for the DPI project.
Basically we have a better idea how to partition our job in implementation.
We still need to come up with the data structure and skeleton of the code
for the Design Review document.

Talked to Jacob on the Power PC side for the DPI.  We now have a brief idea
on how the Power PC, DPI DSP, input DSP, video server and PC are working
together in splicing.

Joined the meeting with Michael and Scott to discuss the new FPGA code
to help detect ES start code.  The biggest good news for DPI from the meeting
is that we plan to implement a start code search which will even check across
transport packet boundaries.  This should greatly simplify the DSP's job
for DPI.

Spent some time to study the recent emails from SCTE's DPI Adhoc group.
Seems to me that according to their latest discussion, our DPI product
will be classified as non-seamless splicer.  I believe we need to keep
a closer look on their discussion and may even voice our opinion, to make
sure that our product will not be down-graded.

